{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idef9f7a19-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db","identifier":"/us/usc/t54/s302705"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"302705"},"text":"§ 302705.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Agreement for review under tribal historic preservation regulations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Council may enter into an agreement with an Indian tribe to permit undertakings on tribal land to be reviewed under tribal historic preservation regulations in place of review under regulations promulgated by the Council to govern compliance with ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t54/s306108"},"text":"section 306108 of this title","children":[],"tail":", if the Council, after consultation with the Indian tribe and appropriate State Historic Preservation Officers, determines that the tribal preservation regulations will afford historic property consideration equivalent to that afforded by the Council’s regulations."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idef9f7a1a-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/287/s3"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–287, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-12-19"},"text":"Dec. 19, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/3201"},"text":"128 Stat. 3201","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idef9f7a1b-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idef9f7a1c-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:table","attrib":{"width":"50%","id":"idef9f7a1d-3a70-11f1-83cd-8a39f388f6db"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:colgroup","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"html:col","attrib":{},"text":null,"children"